Program: Outlook
Title: 07/04/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00fvlf1
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 11 Apr 2011
Prosecutor General Maria Bashir from Herat Province in Afghanistan on the risks she faces. Children in Hungary describe the effects of the toxic sludge that devastated the west of the country last year. James Bailey on his struggle with OCD which inspired him to write his book, Man, Interrupted.